# Reactive Input Patterns

Handle user inputs and events reactively with appropriate timing controls for performance and UX.

## Default Behavior

### Debounce User Text Input

Delay processing until user stops typing. Use for search, filters, and any text input that triggers expensive operations.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Debounced search with immediate UI feedback
export class SearchComponent {
  private readonly destroyRef = inject(DestroyRef);
  
  // Local signal for immediate UI feedback
  searchInput = signal('');
  
  constructor() {
    toObservable(this.searchInput).pipe(
      debounceTime(300),
      distinctUntilChanged(),
      takeUntilDestroyed(this.destroyRef)
    ).subscribe(term => {
      this.store.setSearchTerm(term);
    });
  }
  
  onInput(event: Event) {
    const value = (event.target as HTMLInputElement).value;
    this.searchInput.set(value);  // Immediate UI update
  }
}
```

### Throttle High-Frequency Events

Limit execution rate for scroll, resize, and mouse move events.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Throttled scroll handler
export class InfiniteScrollDirective {
  private readonly ngZone = inject(NgZone);
  
  constructor() {
    this.ngZone.runOutsideAngular(() => {
      fromEvent(window, 'scroll').pipe(
        throttleTime(200),
        takeUntilDestroyed()
      ).subscribe(() => {
        if (this.isNearBottom()) {
          this.ngZone.run(() => this.loadMore.emit());
        }
      });
    });
  }
}
```

## Rationale

1. **Performance** - Prevents excessive API calls, re-renders, and computations.
2. **UX** - Users see immediate feedback (local signal) while expensive operations are batched.
3. **Resource efficiency** - Reduces server load and client processing.

## Documented Exceptions

### 1. No Debounce for Instant Filters (Client-Side Only)

When filtering is purely client-side with small datasets, skip debounce for instant response.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Instant client-side filter (small dataset)
export class SmallListComponent {
  filterText = signal('');
  
  filteredItems = computed(() => {
    const term = this.filterText().toLowerCase();
    return this.items().filter(item => 
      item.name.toLowerCase().includes(term)
    );
  });
  
  onFilter(event: Event) {
    this.filterText.set((event.target as HTMLInputElement).value);
    // No debounce - computed handles it efficiently
  }
}
```

**When to use:** Dataset under ~1000 items, no API calls, simple filter logic.

### 2. No Debounce for Discrete Actions

Button clicks, checkbox toggles, and select changes don't need debounce.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Discrete selection (no debounce needed)
onStatusFilterChange(event: Event) {
  const value = (event.target as HTMLSelectElement).value;
  this.store.setFilter(value as StatusFilter);  // Immediate
}
```

### 3. Longer Debounce for API-Heavy Operations

Increase debounce time for expensive operations or rate-limited APIs.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Longer debounce for API search
toObservable(this.searchInput).pipe(
  debounceTime(500),  // 500ms for API calls (vs 300ms for local)
  distinctUntilChanged(),
  filter(term => term.length >= 3),  // Don't call API for short terms
  switchMap(term => this.searchApi.search(term))
).subscribe(results => this.results.set(results));
```

## Anti-Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ No debounce on API-triggering search
onSearchInput(event: Event) {
  const term = (event.target as HTMLInputElement).value;
  this.api.search(term).subscribe();  // Fires on every keystroke!
}

// ❌ Debounce without distinctUntilChanged
toObservable(this.input).pipe(
  debounceTime(300)
  // Missing distinctUntilChanged - fires even if value unchanged
).subscribe(/* ... */);

// ❌ Throttle on text input (loses characters)
fromEvent(input, 'input').pipe(
  throttleTime(300)  // Wrong: throttle drops events, use debounce
).subscribe(/* ... */);

// ❌ Running scroll handlers in Angular zone
fromEvent(window, 'scroll').pipe(
  throttleTime(100)
).subscribe(() => {
  // Triggers change detection on every throttled event!
});
```

## Combined Filters Pattern

When multiple filters must work together:

```typescript
// ✅ Combined filters with single computed
export const ItemStore = signalStore(
  withState({ items: [], statusFilter: 'all', searchTerm: '' }),
  
  withComputed((store) => ({
    filteredItems: computed(() => {
      let items = store.items();
      
      // Apply status filter
      const status = store.statusFilter();
      if (status !== 'all') {
        items = items.filter(item => item.status === status);
      }
      
      // Apply search filter
      const term = store.searchTerm().toLowerCase().trim();
      if (term.length >= 3) {
        items = items.filter(item =>
          item.name.toLowerCase().includes(term) ||
          item.description.toLowerCase().includes(term)
        );
      }
      
      return items;
    })
  }))
);
```

## Timing Guidelines

| Scenario | Operator | Delay |
|----------|----------|-------|
| Text search (local) | `debounceTime` | 150-300ms |
| Text search (API) | `debounceTime` | 300-500ms |
| Autocomplete | `debounceTime` | 200-300ms |
| Scroll events | `throttleTime` | 100-200ms |
| Resize events | `debounceTime` | 150-250ms |
| Mouse move | `throttleTime` | 16-50ms (frame rate) |

## Complete Pattern: Debounced API Search

```typescript
export class SearchComponent {
  private readonly destroyRef = inject(DestroyRef);
  private readonly searchService = inject(SearchService);
  
  searchInput = signal('');
  results = signal<Result[]>([]);
  isSearching = signal(false);
  
  constructor() {
    toObservable(this.searchInput).pipe(
      debounceTime(300),
      distinctUntilChanged(),
      tap(term => {
        if (term.length >= 3) {
          this.isSearching.set(true);
        }
      }),
      filter(term => term.length >= 3),
      switchMap(term => 
        this.searchService.search(term).pipe(
          catchError(() => of([]))  // Graceful error handling
        )
      ),
      takeUntilDestroyed(this.destroyRef)
    ).subscribe(results => {
      this.results.set(results);
      this.isSearching.set(false);
    });
  }
}
```
